AB  - How might emerging modalities (e.g., NLP) be leveraged to transform th
e provision of parenting support? To explore the role of AI technologi
es in supporting parenting behaviour—and child-well-being—we surveyed 
92 parents to gather their perspectives on nine future-oriented scenar
ios. We used Design Fiction and Speed Dating to understand parents nee
ds and preferences around the design of agent-based supports. We explo
re the perceived benefits of AI assistants (i.e., receiving objective 
feedback, managing emotions and personalised guidance) and the most vo
iced concerns (i.e., AI undermining parental authority, replacing huma
n interactions, and promoting lazy parenting). Finally, we highlight a
 number of plausible design directions based on the scenarios that par
ents were positive about.
